    • getValue

      public <T> T getValue(Class<T> type)
      Values for properties are evaluated in the following order: 1. First check if a system variable with the expected name is set, that is a system variable PREFIX+<PROPERTY-NAME>. If not found, then go to step 2. 2. Check if the value is defined in the properties file ./knowledgelandscape.properties. If not found go to step 3. 3. Use the default value defined in this enumeration.
      Parameters:
      type - The type of the value to retrieve.
      Returns:
      The value in the specified type.
